        <num>CCP 1040</num>
        <heading>1040.  Words &quot;plaintiff&quot; and &quot;defendant&quot; include plaintiff and defendant in an incidental action</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1040.  Words &quot;plaintiff&quot; and &quot;defendant&quot; include plaintiff and defendant in an incidental action
Unless the context clearly indicates otherwise, wherever the words &quot;plaintiff&quot; and &quot;defendant&quot; are used in this Code, they respectively include a plaintiff and a defendant in an incidental demand.</p>
        </content>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111120</p>
        </authorialNote>
